Concepts.Title: Midjourney
Concepts.Description: The Midjourney Style Graph represents the inaugural, major pilot from GraphHub. As we delve into an entirely new world filled with endless discoveries, maintaining an organized archive of all the information can prove challenging. This graph is designed to address this issue by establishing a centralized hub. Here, Midjourney users can collaborate in curating and structuring knowledge in a manner that is orderly, discoverable and sherable.

ConceptMarkdown.Markdown:
### The MidJourney Knowledge Graph

Welcome to the **MidJourney Knowledge Graph**! This tool is designed to assist the community in creating, sharing, collaborating on, and organizing ideas and concepts related to MidJourney and its various facets. The graph facilitates effortless exploration and visualization of the connections between different concepts, which are organized into logical groupings.

#### Introduction

GraphHub, currently in its beta stage, is a versatile tool offering a comprehensive platform for capturing and systematizing information about concepts by categorizing them into coherent lists. Whether you're a user, developer, or enthusiast, this tool is geared to aid you in seamlessly navigating the vast landscape of MidJourney.

#### Features

1. **Knowledge Graph Creation**: The platform facilitates the creation of a dynamic knowledge graph by enabling the addition of concepts and the establishment of connections between various MidJourney concepts. It allows the representation of diverse concepts such as art styles, photography techniques, digital art genres, and virtually any concept of your choosing!

2. **Visual Exploration**: The knowledge graph offers a visually intuitive depiction of the relationships between various MidJourney concepts.

3. **Collaboration and Sharing**: The platform enhances collaboration by allowing you to share your knowledge graph with others. You can invite team members or fellow enthusiasts to contribute their unique insights, annotations, and additions to the graph. This fosters a collaborative ecosystem where ideas can thrive, and knowledge can be collectively constructed.

4. **Export and Integration**: This tool will soon provide native support for exporting all the information, as well as an API for the tech-savvy among you. The tool is open-source, and the complete graph can be found on GitHub.

#### Getting Started

Begin by exploring the lists owned by this concept, currently divided into Styles and Entities. For each of these lists, you'll see all the concepts they encompass, allowing you to delve further by examining the lists they extend.

Clicking on any concept will provide a detailed breakdown of the concept and its associated lists.

#### GraphHub Beta

I'm vigorously working on expanding the functionality to soon enable users to:
1. Search
2. Contribute
3. Administer/Moderate

For ideas or suggestions, feel free to connect with me on [LinkedIn @ Daniel Hai](https://www.linkedin.com/in/daniel-hai/).

Also check out my DevLog which follows the development of GraphHub.

[![IMAGE ALT TEXT](http://img.youtube.com/vi/JJBO2r0F1Ug/0.jpg)](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JJBO2r0F1Ug "Video Title")

### MidJourney Graph Taxonomy and Ontology

The current taxonomy is subject to significant changes, but the general notion at present is to organize things into four levels:

1. Root items (broad lists directly owned by the MidJourney concept)
2. [Domain](/midjourney/concept/3ad98140-45bd-4bc0-b401-24c4d5ca48ef) (Lists falling under a specific domain like Architecture or Photography)
3. [Category](/midjourney/concept/3b57a547-f1d4-47cd-ba0d-9e2a2b4e9789) (When the domain can be further divided, e.g., photography styles and photographers)
4. [Niche](/midjourney/concept/288cbae4-4c53-463a-944e-3ad764bf8848) (Any list that further refines the scope of a category is considered a niche)
